So this word kind of pops up if you've checked the website or the docs.

16:03.680 --> 16:05.040
Democratic tech collectives.

16:05.040 --> 16:09.040
So what is that actually?

16:09.040 --> 16:15.360
We are so Autonomic is a more public registered in the UK.

16:15.360 --> 16:16.800
We're publicly regulated.

16:16.800 --> 16:19.520
We're a cooperative society.

16:19.520 --> 16:26.960
We have gone through the paperwork to make that happen because we wanted to do that.

16:26.960 --> 16:33.460
But we recognize that not everyone will want to do that or be able to do that.

16:33.460 --> 16:35.920
And this really depends on a per country basis.

16:35.920 --> 16:39.000
If you're in the Netherlands, it's a different model.

16:39.000 --> 16:45.560
If you're in the UK, the way you relate to the legal system and the state is like, in

16:45.560 --> 16:46.720
Germany, it's quite difficult.

16:46.720 --> 16:49.600
I've been told there's no way to kind of just like slot yourself in.

16:49.600 --> 16:57.600
You're like, yeah, it's not like very easy to find information.

16:57.600 --> 17:02.040
And we don't want that to be a limiting factor in working together.

17:02.040 --> 17:07.000
So we were trying to conceptualize this idea of like what other groups would we be willing

17:07.000 --> 17:13.880
to work with but not close that definition down from the outside.

17:13.880 --> 17:22.200
So we were thinking about other groups who want to work with their friends or together

17:22.200 --> 17:26.280
with other groups and have set up decision making, for example, collective decision making.

17:26.280 --> 17:31.520
So they're able to navigate what they want to do together.

17:31.520 --> 17:33.560
That was kind of like a thing we wanted to do.

17:33.560 --> 17:35.480
We want to be able to interact with each other.

17:35.480 --> 17:41.320
We want to be able to disagree and receive and send constructive feedback, reach, compromise,

17:41.320 --> 17:43.240
stuff like this.

